Privacy Policy for Ampere Pro

Effective Date: 17.12.2024

This Privacy Policy explains how your personal data is collected, used, and protected by the Ampere Pro application ("we", "our", or "us"). Your privacy is important to us, and we are committed to protecting the information you share with us. By using the Ampere Pro application, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this policy.

1. Information Collection and Use

Ampere Pro does not collect any personal data, nor does it require an internet connection or access to any network. The application works solely with the device’s sensors to provide battery-related information. It does not gather any data about you or your device beyond what is needed to display the battery status and related metrics.

2. No Advertisements

Ampere Pro does not display any advertisements, and it does not share any data with third parties for advertising purposes. We respect your privacy and do not track or use your information for marketing or advertising.

3. Permissions

The app may request certain permissions to access the device’s sensors, such as the battery status, but these permissions are only used for the functioning of the application and will not be shared or used for any other purpose.

4. Data Security

Since no personal or sensitive information is collected or stored by Ampere Pro, there is no risk of data breach or unauthorized access. The app is designed to protect the privacy of its users by avoiding unnecessary data collection.

5. Changes to This Privacy Policy

We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the app or on this page. It is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically for any updates.

6. Contact Us

If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our practices, feel free to contact us at:

drfsdev@outlook.com
